The paper proposes a deep generative machine learning architecture for cancer diagnosis using microarray data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of microarray data suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on cancer diagnosis suggests that the paper may also belong to the Bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-category.
